<div type="old-chinese-contrasts">
<p>1. Some words express criticism that is presupposed to be correct (zé 責 ) or is at least typically supposed to be incorrect (bàng 謗 ), others express criticism that is clearly presupposed to false (zèn 譖, chán 讒, zhuó 諑 ).</p>
<p>2. Some words primarily denote face-to-face criticism (jié 訐 ); others always denote criticism behind one's back (fěi 誹 ).</p>
<p>3. Some words express strong criticism likely to lead to punitive action or open conflict (huǐ 毀 ), others express slight dissatisfaction without any implication of future strong punitive action (zǐ 訾 ).</p>
